The Telegraph - Calcutta (Kolkata) | Sports | Liverpool to miss Gerrard
                                                                                                                                                                                                     Liverpool to miss Gerrard
                      
	London: Liverpool will go into Saturdays Premier League match against Fulham without captain Steven Gerrard who has failed to recover from a torn groin muscle that kept him out of Englands 2-1 victory at Germany on Wednesday.         
	Chelsea will also be without striker Didier Drogba who starts a three-match ban. Frank Lampard, who also did not play against Germany because of a rib injury, is set to play Saturdays match against Newcastle.         
	Arsene Wenger has problems as Arsenal try to revive their title challenge at Manchester City.         
	Defender Kolo Toure is ruled out with a calf injury while Theo Walcott is sidelined for three months because of surgery on his dislocated shoulder.           (AGENCIES)                                                                                                                      
